  "prompt": "How can I remove the HTC One X System folder, which still appears on my Windows 7 list of devices?",
  "response": "To remove the HTC One X system folder that appears on your Windows 7 list of devices, you can follow these steps. It\u2019s important to note that this process involves modifying Windows Device Manager or using the Registry Editor, so proceed with caution.\n\n### Method 1: Uninstall the Device via Device Manager\n\n1. **Open Device Manager**:\n   - Right-click on the \u201cComputer\u201d icon on your desktop or in the Start Menu.\n   - Select \u201cManage\u201d and then click on \u201cDevice Manager\u201d.\n\n2. **Locate Your Device**:\n   - Look for your HTC One X under categories such as \"Portable Devices\" or \"Universal Serial Bus controllers\".\n\n3. **Uninstall the Device**:\n   - Right-click on your HTC One X and select \u201cUninstall\u201d.\n   - If prompted, check the option to delete the driver software for this device (if applicable).\n   - Click \u201cOK\u201d to confirm.\n\n4. **Restart Your Computer**:\n   - Restart Windows, and after the reboot, it should no longer appear in the list of devices.\n\n### Method 2: Remove Device Registry Entries\n\nIf the device still appears after you've uninstalled it, you may need to remove its registry entry.\n\n1. **Open Registry Editor**:\n   - Press `Win + R` to open the Run dialog.\n   - Type `regedit` and press `Enter`.\n\n2. **Backup Your Registry**:\n   - Before making changes, it\u2019s a good idea to back up the registry.\n   - Click on \u201cFile\u201d > \u201cExport\u201d, choose a location, and save it.\n\n3. **Navigate to Device Key**:\n   - Go to the following path:\n     ```\n     HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Enum\\USB\n     ```\n   - Look for any subkeys that relate to your HTC One X device.\n\n4. **Delete the Device Key**:\n   - Once you find the corresponding key, right-click on it and select \u201cDelete\u201d.\n   - Confirm the deletion.\n\n5. **Restart Your Computer**:\n   - Restart your PC for the changes to take effect.\n\n### Method 3: Clean Up Unnecessary Drivers\n\n1. **Use a Driver Cleanup Tool**:\n   - You can use programs like Driver Cleaner or other third-party tools specifically designed to remove old drivers that are no longer in use.\n\n### Additional Note\n\nBe cautious when using the Registry Editor since improper changes can affect your system's stability. If you are not comfortable with editing the registry, it may be best to consult someone who is more experienced or to avoid this method altogether.\n\nIf the HTC One X folder continues to appear after following these methods, ensure that no software associated with the device is installed, such as HTC Sync Manager, as it might recreate registry entries related to the device. Removing or uninstalling such software can also help in clearing the system folder.",
